Sam Kass, the Executive Director of the First Lady's Let's Move! initiative and the first-ever White House Senior Policy Advisor on Nutrition, is leaving the White House at the end of the month. Kass has played a key role in developing nutrition policy and has been a personal chef to the First Family. President Obama praised Kass for his work in inspiring families and children to lead healthier lives, while First Lady Michelle Obama highlighted his legacy of progress in improving food options and marketing to children. Kass will remain involved with the Let's Move! initiative, and his successor will be announced in the new year.